main event: A radar object was observed for 6 minutes, appearing as a planet or bright star and covering a 60 degree arc in 4.5 seconds.
interesting points: The object was observed at an elevation of 12 degrees.
The data on the object was considered inconclusive and the case was carried as having insufficient data.
A similar object was observed by a USS Falcon, covering 62 degrees of arc in 45 seconds at an elevation of 15-15 degrees above the horizon.
The USS Falcon sighting was suspected to be a duplicate of a previous report (APIN 9857).
The sightings occurred in November 1963 in the Pacific Ocean area around 40N 174W.
